.TH oparesolvehfiport 1 "Intel Corporation" "Copyright(C) 2015\-2015" "Master map: IFSFFCLIRG (Man Page)" 
.SH NAME
oparesolvehfiport

.NL

.PP

\fB(Host)\fR
Permits the Intel(R) Omni-Path Fabric Host Software style Intel(R) Omni-Path Host Fabric Interface (HFI) number and port number arguments to be converted to a Host Software style HFI name and physical port number. This can be useful when writing scripts that can accept FastFabric -style arguments, and interact directly with OFED commands.
.SH Syntax
.NL
oparesolvehfiport \fIhfi\fR \fIport\fR or
.PP

.br
oparesolvehfiport --help

.br

.SH Options
.NL

.SH Options
.NL

.TP 10
--help 
.NL
Produces full help text.

.TP 10
 \fIhfi\fR 
.NL
HFI to send by. Numbered 1..n. 0 = system-wide port num. Default is first HFI.

.TP 10
 \fIport\fR 
.NL
Port to send by. Numbered 1..n. 0 (default) is first active port.

.TP 10
\fB-h and -p options permit a variety of selections:\fR
.NL

.TP 10
-h 0 -p 0 
.NL
First active port in system.

.TP 10
-h \fIx\fR-p 0 
.NL
First active port on HFI \fIx\fR.

.TP 10
-h 0 -p \fIy\fR 
.NL
Port \fIy \fR within system (no matter which ports are active).

.TP 10
-h \fIx\fR-p \fIy\fR 
.NL
HFI \fIx\fR, port \fIy\fR

.SH Examples 
.NL
oparesolvehfiport 0 1
.br
Output:
.br
    hfi\(ul0:1
